# Cursor — PR & CI

Authoritative source: [docs/ai/pr-and-ci.md](mdc:docs/ai/pr-and-ci.md).

## PR title (CI-enforced)

Regex from [`.github/workflows/pr-checks.yml`](mdc:.github/workflows/pr-checks.yml):

```
^(feat|fix|chore|build|ci|docs|style|refactor|perf|test)(\([-a-zA-Z0-9,]+\))!?:
```

Format: `verb(scope): description` — scope is single word or
comma-separated. For breaking changes: `verb(scope)!: description`.

Examples taken from recent merged history:

- `feat(frontend): expose newUserSignupsAllowed backend method`
- `fix(frontend): correct error ordering in assertCkEthAmount when amount is below ledger fee`
- `refactor(frontend): extract AiAssistantChat component`
- `chore(frontend): Update llm files`
- `feat(backend)!: Add rate limiter to cycle-sensitive methods`
- `feat(backend): Add /status endpoint for signup-rate monitoring`
- `chore(release): v2.0.5`
- `test(frontend): Update Vitest coverage thresholds`
- `chore(e2e): Update Playwright E2E Snapshots`
- `docs(readme): add Ops section and table of contents`
- `chore(npm-deps-dev): bump @tailwindcss/postcss from 4.2.1 to 4.2.2`

Common scopes: `frontend`, `backend`, `e2e`, `ci`, `devops`, `build`,
`release`, `npm-deps-dev`, `npm-deps`, `readme`, `ai` (for these AI docs).

## PR body (template)

Honor [`.github/pull_request_template.md`](mdc:.github/pull_request_template.md):

```markdown
# Motivation

<!-- Why this change exists. 1–3 sentences. -->

# Changes

<!-- Bulleted list of what changed. Mention if you updated docs/ai/**. -->

# Tests

<!-- New / updated tests, or manual repro steps for visual / e2e changes. -->
```

All three sections required. **No Jira / Atlassian links** —
`check-pr-description` rejects URLs matching `*.atlassian.*` or `*.jira.*`.

## Atomicity

One logical change per PR. If you write "and also" / "while I was here" /
"I noticed that" → split. Recent merged PRs show what good size looks like
(one component extraction, one util fix, one new endpoint).

## Local gates (run before opening the PR)

```bash
# Frontend (always)
npm run format
npm run lint -- --max-warnings 0
npm run check
npm run test

# i18n (only if you edited en.json)
npm run i18n

# Bindings (only if you changed backend.did or Rust public API)
npm run generate

# Backend (only if you edited Rust)
./scripts/format.sh
./scripts/lint.rust.sh
./scripts/lint.did.sh
./scripts/lint.cargo-workspace-dependencies.sh
./scripts/test.backend.sh   # heavy
```

## CI jobs you must keep green

- `pr-checks / check-pr-title` — title regex.
- `pr-checks / check-pr-description` — no Jira / Atlassian URLs.
- `pr-checks / check-empty-pr` — at least one changed file.
- `frontend-checks / format` — auto-commits formatting on non-fork PRs.
- `frontend-checks / lint` — `npm run lint -- --max-warnings 0`.
- `frontend-checks / check` — `npm run check` + `npm run check:tests`.
- `frontend-checks / test` (sharded 20×) + `test-coverage`.
- `frontend-checks / lockfile` — `npm run lint:lockfile`.
- `frontend-checks / config` — IC domain validation.
- `backend-checks / lint` — clippy + candid lint (only when Rust changed).
- `backend-checks / workspace-dependencies` — workspace-only deps.
- `backend-tests / tests` — pocket-ic integration tests.
- `backend-tests / breaking-interface` — refuses `.did` changes without
  `!:` + `BREAKING CHANGE:` markers.
- `formatting-checks / format` — Rust + shell formatting.
- `e2e-tests` — Playwright (full run is gated on `run-e2e-snapshots`
  label).
- `repo-checks`, `devops-checks`, `binding-checks` — auxiliary gates.

Never silence a failure with `// eslint-disable` / `// @ts-ignore` /
`it.skip` / `#[allow(…)]` without explicit user approval.

## Updating an existing PR

- **Add commits.** Never `git push --force` to a PR branch. Don't amend
  pushed commits with `git commit --amend`. Don't rebase a PR onto `main`
  to "tidy history" — let the merge group handle it.
- **What counts as "the user explicitly asks":** the user uses the
  literal words "force-push", "amend", "rebase", or "rewrite history"
  in their request, **or** selects a multi-choice option whose label
  itself contains those words. Phrases like "do what you think is
  best", "do what's most correct", "do it your way", or general
  approval of a stacked-PR plan **DO NOT** count. When in doubt,
  add a new commit — squash-merge will tidy history at merge time.
- When offering choices, the **default** must always be the
  no-force-push option. Do not put a force-push option first, and do
  not pick a force-push option in response to delegated decisions.

## Bot-approved files

[`.github/repo_policies/BOT_APPROVED_FILES`](mdc:.github/repo_policies/BOT_APPROVED_FILES)
lists the paths bots may modify in automated PRs (snapshots, generated
icons, locked files, etc.). Don't commit changes to other paths from a bot
context — humans review those.
